Author:
Vol / Page:  2
Edition:
Quote:  The <i>Inflexible</i> has returned from a cruise, undetaken for the purpose of finding  site, which should be at once distant from Auckland, and suitable for the location of the newly-arrived pensioners. Why the original intention of establishing this Military settlement near the capital, as recommended in Lord Grey's dispatch, should have been abandoned - if, in truth, it has been abandoned - is easy enough to understand, although the want of absolute and certai[n] knowledge disincline one to risk asserting as much in express terms.
